--setting values before everything runs so there is no "nil" error zoom = 1 yb=0 xb=0 h=0 function onTick() --button position and sizes ButtonPlus = {x=30,y=h-29,r=9} ButtonMinus = {x=30,y=h-20,r=9} ButtonUp = {x=12,y=h-29,r=9} ButtonDown = {x=12,y=h-11,r=9} ButtonLeft = {x=3,y=h-20,r=9} ButtonRight = {x=21,y=h-20,r=9} ButtonReset = {x=12,y=h-20,r=9}
--inputs TouchX = input.getNumber(3)--touchscreen X input TouchY = input.getNumber(4)--touchscreen Y input Touchinput = input.getBool(1)--touchscreen touch input x = input.getNumber(7)--vehicle x position y = input.getNumber(8)--vehicle y position
if Touchinput == true then -- touch check if TouchX >= ButtonPlus.x and TouchX <= ButtonPlus.x+ButtonPlus.r then if TouchY >= ButtonPlus.y and TouchY <= ButtonPlus.y+ButtonPlus.r then zoom = zoom-0.05 elseif TouchY >= ButtonMinus.y and TouchY <= ButtonMinus.y+ButtonMinus.r then zoom = zoom+0.05 end end
if TouchX >= ButtonUp.x and TouchX <= ButtonUp.x+ButtonUp.r then --x position check if TouchY >= ButtonUp.y and TouchY <= ButtonUp.y+ButtonUp.r then --y position check yb = yb+(10*zoom) --changes value when all checks are true end end
if TouchX >= ButtonDown.x and TouchX <= ButtonDown.x+ButtonDown.r then if TouchY >= ButtonDown.y and TouchY <= ButtonDown.y+ButtonDown.r then yb = yb-(10*zoom) end end
if TouchX >= ButtonLeft.x and TouchX <= ButtonLeft.x+ButtonLeft.r then if TouchY >= ButtonLeft.y and TouchY <= ButtonLeft.y+ButtonLeft.r then xb = xb-(10*zoom) end end
if TouchX >= ButtonRight.x and TouchX <= ButtonRight.x+ButtonRight.r then if TouchY >= ButtonRight.y and TouchY <= ButtonRight.y+ButtonRight.r then xb = xb+(10*zoom) end end
if TouchX >= ButtonReset.x and TouchX <= ButtonReset.x+ButtonReset.r then if TouchY >= ButtonReset.y and TouchY <= ButtonReset.y+ButtonReset.r then xb = 0 yb = 0 end end
end --clamp of zoom value if zoom < 0.1 then zoom = 0.1 end if zoom > 50 then zoom = 50 end
end function onDraw() --getting size of the screen w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.drawMap(x+xb, y+yb, zoom) --drawing map
pixelX, pixelY = map.mapToScreen(x+xb, y+yb, zoom, w, h, x, y) --checking vehicle position to point on map screen.setColor(255,0,0)--selecting red color screen.drawRectF(pixelX, pixelY, 1,1)--drawing point on map where vehicle is
screen.setColor(50,50,50,150)--selecting background color for buttons --drawing background for buttons screen.drawRectF(ButtonPlus.x,ButtonPlus.y,ButtonPlus.r,ButtonPlus.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonMinus.x,ButtonMinus.y,ButtonMinus.r,ButtonMinus.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonUp.x,ButtonUp.y,ButtonUp.r,ButtonUp.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonDown.x,ButtonDown.y,ButtonMinus.r,ButtonDown.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonLeft.x,ButtonLeft.y,ButtonLeft.r,ButtonLeft.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonRight.x,ButtonRight.y,ButtonRight.r,ButtonRight.r) screen.drawRectF(ButtonReset.x,ButtonReset.y,ButtonReset.r,ButtonReset.r)
screen.setColor(0,255,0,200)--selecting colors for buttons --drawing text on buttons screen.drawText((ButtonPlus.x)+3,(ButtonPlus.y)+2,"+") screen.drawText((ButtonMinus.x)+3,(ButtonMinus.y)+2,"-") screen.drawText((ButtonUp.x)+3,(ButtonUp.y)+2,"^") screen.drawText((ButtonDown.x)+3,(ButtonDown.y)+2,".") screen.drawText((ButtonLeft.x)+3,(ButtonLeft.y)+2,"<") screen.drawText((ButtonRight.x)+3,(ButtonRight.y)+2,">") screen.drawText((ButtonReset.x)+3,(ButtonReset.y)+2,"R") end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() processNumber = input.getNumber(1) maxNumber = input.getNumber(2) minNumber = input.getNumber(3)
angle = (processNumber/(math.abs(minNumber-maxNumber)))*270 end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() width = screen.getWidth() height = screen.getHeight() --Clear screen before render screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
--Render background screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawCircle(width/2,height/2,width/2*0.75) --Draw Circle
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTriangleF(width/2,height/2,0,height,width,height) --Cut triangle from circle screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawLine(width/2,height/2+1,math.cos(math.rad(135))*width/2*0.75+width/2,math.sin(math.rad(135))*width/2*0.75+width/2) screen.drawLine(width/2,height/2+1,math.cos(math.rad(45))*width/2*0.75+width/2,math.sin(math.rad(45))*width/2*0.75+width/2)
--Render Indicator screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawLine(width/2,height/2,math.cos(math.rad(angle+135))*width/2*0.65+width/2,math.sin(math.rad(angle+135))*width/2*0.65+height/2)
--Render text. textRN = math.floor(processNumber*10)/10
screen.drawText(width/2-(string.len(textRN)*5)/2+1,height*0.75,textRN)
end

if Up < 0 then B = 180-B end --(asin((sin(x*pi2))/(sin((90-y)*(pi/180)))))*(180/pi) output.setNumber(23, B) output.setNumber(24, P) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() C = w/2 M = h/2 BR = math.rad(B) SB = math.sin(BR) CB = math.cos(BR) IC = C + (P*SB) * w/180 IM = M + (P*CB) * w/180 L = (w+h)*2
--screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, 200) --screen.drawText(0, 0, B)
screen.setColor(32, 64, 96, 200) screen.drawTriangleF(-CB*L+IC, SB*L+IM, CB*L+IC, -SB*L+IM, -SB*L+IC, -CB*L+IM)
screen.setColor(32, 16, 0, 200) screen.drawTriangleF(-CB*L+IC, SB*L+IM, CB*L+IC, -SB*L+IM, SB*L+IC, CB*L+IM)
screen.setColor(255, 0, 0, 255) Xline(-90, 10, 2*w/32) Xline(90, 10, 2*w/32)
screen.setColor(255, 255, 255, 160) subline(-15*w/180*SB, -15*h/180*CB, 2*w/32) subline(-30*w/180*SB, -30*h/180*CB, 4*w/32) subline(-45*w/180*SB, -45*h/180*CB, 2*w/32) subline(-60*w/180*SB, -60*h/180*CB, 6*w/32) subline(-75*w/180*SB, -75*h/180*CB, 2*w/32)
subline(15*w/180*SB, 15*h/180*CB, 2*w/32) subline(30*w/180*SB, 30*h/180*CB, 4*w/32) subline(45*w/180*SB, 45*h/180*CB, 2*w/32) subline(60*w/180*SB, 60*h/180*CB, 6*w/32) subline(75*w/180*SB, 75*h/180*CB, 2*w/32)
screen.setColor(255, 120, 0, 160) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2 - 13*w/32*SB, h/2 - 13*h/32*CB, w/2 - 10*w/32*math.sin(BR-1/6), h/2 - 10*h/32*math.cos(BR-1/6), w/2 - 10*w/32*math.sin(BR+1/6), h/2 - 10*h/32*math.cos(BR+1/6))
end
function subline(X, Y, len) screen.drawLine((-len*CB)+X+IC, (len*SB)+Y+IM, (len*CB)+X+IC, (-len*SB)+Y+IM) end
function Xline(deg, degD, len) X1 = (deg - degD) * w/180 * SB Y1 = (deg - degD) * h/180 * CB X2 = (deg + degD) * w/180 * SB Y2 = (deg + degD) * h/180 * CB screen.drawLine((-len*CB)+X1+IC, (len*SB)+Y1+IM, (len*CB)+X2+IC, (-len*SB)+Y2+IM) screen.drawLine((-len*CB)+X2+IC, (len*SB)+Y2+IM, (len*CB)+X1+IC, (-len*SB)+Y1+IM) end

end

FD_0 = false FD_1 = false FD = false
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.setColor(200,100,0,255) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2-3*w/32, h/2+3*h/32, w/2, h/2+3*h/32, w/2, h/2) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2+3*w/32, h/2+3*h/32, w/2, h/2+3*h/32, w/2, h/2) screen.drawLine(w/2-10*w/32, h/2-1, w/2-6*w/32, h/2-1) screen.drawLine(w/2+6*w/32, h/2-1, w/2+10*w/32, h/2-1)
screen.setColor(128,128,128,255) screen.drawLine(0, h/2-1, 3*w/32, h/2-1) screen.drawLine(w-3*w/32, h/2-1, w, h/2-1) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2-4*w/32, 0, w/2, 0, w/2, 4*h/32) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2+4*w/32, 0, w/2, 0, w/2, 4*h/32)
rMark(math.pi*1/3, 3) rMark(math.pi*-1/3, 3) rMark(math.pi*1/6, 3) rMark(math.pi*-1/6, 3) rMark(math.pi*1/16, 3) rMark(math.pi*-1/16, 3)
if ResetBTN then screen.drawRectF(TW/2-2*(TW/32), TH-5*(TH/32), 4*(TW/32), 4*(TH/32)) end
if FD_1 then screen.drawRectF(0, TH-7, 6, 7) end
if FD then screen.setColor(0,255,0,255) else screen.setColor(128,128,128,255) end
screen.drawTextBox(1, TH-7, 5, 7, "F", 0, 0)
end
function onTick() TW = input.getNumber(1) TH = input.getNumber(2) inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4)
B = input.getNumber(23) P = input.getNumber(24)
isPressed = input.getBool(1) ResetBTN = isPressed and isInRect(inputX, inputY, TW/2-3*(TW/32), TH-6*(TH/32), 6*(TW/32), 6*(TH/32))
FD_1 = isPressed and isInRect(inputX, inputY, 0, TH-7, 6, 7)
if FD_1 and not FD_0 and not FD then FD = true elseif FD_1 and not FD_0 and FD then FD = false end FD_0 = FD_1
C = TW/2 M = TH/2 BR = math.rad(B) CB = math.cos(BR) IM = M + (P*CB) output.setBool(32, ResetBTN) output.setBool(31, FD)
end
function rMark(deg, length) if deg > 0 then offset_w = -1 else offset_w = 0 end screen.drawLine(w/2 + offset_w - w * math.sin(deg), h/2 -1 - h * math.cos(deg), w/2 + offset_w - (w/2 - length) * math.sin(deg), h/2 -1 - (h/2 - length) * math.cos(deg)) end
function isInRect(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end

object.script:
tilt = 0 rollAngle = 0 vertCheck = true lineDist = property.getNumber('Degrees per Line') pixPerDegree = property.getNumber('Pixels per Degree') maxLineWidth = property.getNumber('Maximum Line Length as Screen Percent') lineDivideFactor = (property.getNumber('Minimum Line Length as Percent of Max')+1)*90 if property.getBool('Vertical Flip') then yMod = -1 else yMod = 1 end
function onTick() tilt = input.getNumber(1)*360 -- Tilt (Forward tilt sensor) supplied through composite 1 maxAngle = 90-math.abs(tilt) rollAngle = (input.getNumber(2)*360)/maxAngle*90 -- Roll (Right tilt sensor) supplied through composite 2 vertCheck = input.getNumber(3)>=0 if not vertCheck then -- Vertical check (Up tilt sensor) supplied through composite 3 tilt = tilt*-1 rollAngle = rollAngle*-1 end end
function calcXY(x,y,bearing,distance) bearing = math.rad(bearing + 90) y = y+math.cos(bearing) * -distance x = x+math.sin(bearing) * distance return x,y end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if vertCheck then screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) end for lineAngle = -90, 90, lineDist do if lineAngle>0 and vertCheck then screen.setColor(50,50,50) elseif lineAngle>0 and not vertCheck then screen.setColor(50,50,50) end lineLen = (maxLineWidth*w)*(1-math.abs(lineAngle)/lineDivideFactor) currentY = (tilt-lineAngle)*pixPerDegree*yMod mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,currentY) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,lineLen/2) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,lineLen/2) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) end centerY = h/2+tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod screen.setColor(125,125,125) mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,100) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,100) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawRectF(w/2,h/2,2,2) end

autoDepth = false depth = 0 function onTick() pressed = input.getBool(1) and not down down = input.getBool(1) xR = input.getNumber(1) yR = input.getNumber(2) x = input.getNumber(3) y = input.getNumber(4) alt = input.getNumber(10) output.setNumber(1,depth) --depth = input.getNumber(11)
if isPointInRectangle(x,y,2, yR-14, xR-4, 12) and pressed then --toggle autoDepth = not autoDepth depth = alt --sets depth to current alt end if autoDepth then output.setBool(1,true) else output.setBool(1,false) end
if isPointInRectangle(x,y,2, 4, xR/2-3, yR/2-4) and down and depth<-0.1 then --up goUp = true depth = depth+0.1 else goUp = false end if isPointInRectangle(x,y,xR/2+1, 4, xR/2-3, yR/2-4) and down then -- down goDown = true depth = depth-0.1 else goDown = false end end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if autoDepth then screen.setColor(150,150,150) screen.drawRectF(2, h-14, w-4, 12) screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(2, h-14, w-4, 12, math.floor(-depth), 0,0) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) screen.drawRectF(2, h-14, w-4, 12) screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(2, h-14, w-4, 12, "set", 0,0) end
if goUp and autoDepth then screen.setColor(150,150,150) screen.drawRectF(2, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) screen.drawRectF(2, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4) end
if goDown and autoDepth then screen.setColor(150,150,150) screen.drawRectF(w/2+1, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) screen.drawRectF(w/2+1, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4) end
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(3, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4, "+", 0,0) screen.drawTextBox(w/2+2, 4, w/2-3, h/2-4, "-", 0,0)
if down then screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRectF(x, y, 1, 1) end
--screen.drawTextBox(x, y, w, h, string.format("%.2f", depth), h_align, v_align) end

object.script:
time = 0 lineIterations = 40 lI = lineIterations heightOffset = 15 hO = heightOffset recRotS = {} recRotC = {} recDist = {} depth = 0 altNorm = 0 zoom = 1 zoomIn = false zoomOut = false
for i = 1,lI do recRotS[i] = 0 recRotC[i] = 0 recDist[i] = 0 end
function onTick() warning = input.getBool(32) inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1)
rot = (input.getNumber(11)+1)*math.pi*0.5 dist = input.getNumber(12) heading = input.getNumber(16) marginLR = property.getNumber("marginLR") speed = 1 time = time+10
alt = input.getNumber(14)*-1 dist2 = input.getNumber(15) depth = alt+dist2 altNorm = alt/depth
if time>=speed then table.insert(recRotS,math.sin(rot)) table.insert(recRotC,math.cos(rot)) table.insert(recDist,dist) time=0
while #recRotS>lI do table.remove(recRotS,1) table.remove(recRotC,1) table.remove(recDist,1) end end
if isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 10, 10, 7, 7) and isPressed and zoom<1 then --zoom in zoom = zoom+0.01 zoomIn = true else zoomIn = false end if isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 10, 19, 7, 7) and isPressed and zoom>0.1 then --zoom out zoom = zoom-0.01 zoomOut = true else zoomOut = false end end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() cx=w/2 h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if zoomIn then screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRectF(11,11,7,7) screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(11,10,8,8,"+",0,0) else screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRect(11,10,6,6) screen.drawTextBox(11,10,8,8,"+",0,0) end if zoomOut then screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRectF(11,20,7,7) screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(11,19,8,8,"-",0,0) else screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRect(11,19,6,6) screen.drawTextBox(11,19,8,8,"-",0,0) end
screen.setColor(100,100,100) screen.drawLine(20,11,20,25)--v screen.drawLine(19,10,22,10)--ht screen.drawLine(19,25,22,25)--hb
screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawLine(19,26-(15*zoom),22,26-(15*zoom))
if isPressed then screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRectF(inputX,inputY,1,1) end
for i = 1,lI do screen.setColor(255, 255, 255,255*(i/lI)) screen.drawRectF((w/4*3)-(zoom*recRotS[i]*recDist[i]),hO-(zoom*recRotC[i]*recDist[i]),1,1) end
screen.setColor(100,100,100) screen.drawLine((w/4*3),hO,(w/4*3)-(zoom*recRotS[lI]*recDist[lI]),hO-(zoom*recRotC[lI]*recDist[lI]))
screen.setColor(100,100,100) --depth part screen.drawLine(w-3,16,w-3,45) screen.drawLine(w-4,45,w-1,45)--hb screen.drawLine(w-4,15,w-1,15)
screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawLine(w-4,(30*altNorm)+15,w-1,(30*altNorm)+15)
screen.drawTextBox(w-35,(30*altNorm)+9,30,10,math.floor(alt*10)/10,1,0) screen.drawTextBox(w-31,45,30,10,string.format("%.1f",depth),1,0)
offset= heading-math.floor(heading/5)*5 --compass ticks2= math.ceil((cx-marginLR-offset)/5) x= cx-offset-ticks2*5 h5= math.floor(heading-cx+x)%360
screen.setColor(255,255,255) while(x<w-marginLR) do if (h5/15==math.floor(h5/15)) then screen.drawLine(x, 0, x, 2) if x<w/2-12 or x>w/2+12 then if h5==0 then screen.drawText(x-2, 3, "n") elseif h5==45 then screen.drawText(x-4,3,"ne") elseif h5==90 then screen.drawText(x-2, 3, "e") elseif h5==135 then screen.drawText(x-4,3,"se") elseif h5==180 then screen.drawText(x-2, 3, "s") elseif h5==225 then screen.drawText(x-4,3,"sw") elseif h5==270 then screen.drawText(x-2, 3, "w") elseif h5==315 then screen.drawText(x-4,3,"nw") end end else screen.drawLine(x, 0, x, 1) end x=x+5 h5=(h5+5)%360 end screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawLine(cx, 0, cx, 2) number=string.format("%1.0f", heading) screen.drawText((w-number:len()*5)/2+1, 3, number)
screen.setColor(255,0,0) if warning then screen.drawTextBox(0,-w/4,w,h,"HATCH OPEN",0,0) end
end

object.script:

function onTick() rX = input.getNumber(1) rY = input.getNumber(2) inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1) water = input.getNumber(10) maxWater = input.getNumber(11)/3 waterNorm = water/maxWater
isPressingFill = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, rX-17, 6, 14, 7) isPressingEmpty = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, rX-17, 21, 14, 7)
if water > maxWater then filling = false full = true else full = false end
if water == 0 then emptying = false end
if isPressingFill and full == false then filling = toggleBool(filling) end if isPressingEmpty and water > 0 then emptying = toggleBool(emptying) end
output.setBool(1,filling) output.setBool(2,emptying) end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if filling then screen.setColor(150,150,150) screen.drawRectF(w-17, 6, 14, 7) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) screen.drawRectF(w-17, 6, 14, 7) end
if emptying then screen.setColor(150,150,150) screen.drawRectF(w-17, 21, 14, 7) else screen.setColor(50,50,50) screen.drawRectF(w-17, 21, 14, 7) end
screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawTextBox(w-17, 5, 14, 7, "F", 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(w-17, 20, 14, 7, "E", 0, 0)
screen.setColor(255,255,255,15) screen.drawRectF(3,h-4,10,-h+10) screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawRectF(3,h-4,10,(-h+10)*waterNorm) end
function toggleBool(tBool) return (not tBool) end

object.script:
tilt = 0 rollAngle = 0 vertCheck = true lineDist = property.getNumber('Degrees per Line') pixPerDegree = property.getNumber('Pixels per Degree') maxLineWidth = property.getNumber('Maximum Line Length as Screen Percent') lineDivideFactor = (property.getNumber('Minimum Line Length as Percent of Max')+1)*90 if property.getBool('Vertical Flip') then yMod = -1 else yMod = 1 end
function onTick() tilt = input.getNumber(1)*360 -- Tilt (Forward tilt sensor) supplied through composite 1 maxAngle = 90-math.abs(tilt) rollAngle = (input.getNumber(2)*360)/maxAngle*90 -- Roll (Right tilt sensor) supplied through composite 2 vertCheck = input.getNumber(3)>=0 if not vertCheck then -- Vertical check (Up tilt sensor) supplied through composite 3 tilt = tilt*-1 rollAngle = rollAngle*-1 end end
function calcXY(x,y,bearing,distance) bearing = math.rad(bearing + 90) y = y+math.cos(bearing) * -distance x = x+math.sin(bearing) * distance return x,y end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0,0,0) screen.drawClear()
if vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,0,100) else screen.setColor(0,240,255) end for lineAngle = -90, 90, lineDist do if lineAngle>0 and vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,240,255) elseif lineAngle>0 and not vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,0,100) end lineLen = (maxLineWidth*w)*(1-math.abs(lineAngle)/lineDivideFactor) currentY = (tilt-lineAngle)*pixPerDegree*yMod mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,currentY) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,lineLen/2) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,lineLen/2) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) end centerY = h/2+tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod screen.setColor(50,50,50) mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,100) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,100) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawRectF(w/2-1,h/2,2,2) end
